SIMPLE: insomuch
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insomuch
<hw>In`so*much"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>So; to such a
degree; in such wise; -- followed by <xex>that</xex> or <xex>as</xex>,
and formerly sometimes by both. Cf. <er>Inasmuch</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Insomusch</qex> as that field is called . . . Aceldama.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts i. 19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Simonides was an excellent poet, <qex>insomuch</qex> that he made
his fortune by it.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insonorous</ent>⟦br⟧
